{"title_page": "Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2009}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox government agency\n|name            = Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board\n|logo            = \n|logo_width      = \n|logo_caption    = \n|motto           = \n|seal            = \n|seal_width      =\n|seal_caption    = \n|formed          = {{start date|1965}}\n|preceding1      =\n|jurisdiction    =\n|headquarters    = [[Austin, Texas]], [[U.S.]]\n|employees       = 233\n|budget          = \n|chief1_name     = Harrison Keller\n|chief1_position = Commissioner\n|chief2_name     =\n|chief2_position =\n|date1           =\n|date1_name      =\n|department      =\n|child1_agency   =\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.thecb.state.tx.us|www.thecb.state.tx.us}}\n}}\n\n[[File:THECBAustinTX.JPG|thumb|Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board headquarters]]\n\n{{Education in the U.S.}}\nThe '''Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board''' ('''THECB''') is an agency of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Texas]]'s government that oversees all public post-secondary education in the state. It is headquartered at 1200 East Anderson Lane in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Welcome to the Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/ |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\nTHECB determines which Texas public four-year universities are permitted to start or continue degree programs. THECB also evaluates degrees from other states and other nations for use in Texas. However, operations of the various universities or systems are the responsibility of each university or system [[board of regents]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Agency Mission, Vision, Philosophy, Core Values, & Key Functions |url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/about-us/board-commissioner/agency-mission-vision-philosophy-core-values-key-functions/ |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 1998 to 2003, it developed a new higher-education plan for the state, called \"Closing the Gaps by 2015\". The plan's stated goal was closing education gaps within Texas, as well as between Texas and other U.S. states. The four main goals of closing the gap was to close the gaps in student participation, student success, excellence and research. Approximately 47,500 additional students will need to enroll at public, independent, and career institutions in fall 2015 to reach the final goal of adding about 630,000 students since fall 2000.\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Closing the Gaps 2015 Progress Report|url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/index.cfm?objectid=858D2E7C-F5C8-97E9-0CDEB3037C1C2CA3|website=The Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe board consists of nine members and one non\u2013voting student representative, all of whom are appointed by the [[Governor of Texas]] on a staggered basis. The terms for the voting members are for six years, ending on August 31 of odd-numbered years while the student representative serves a one year term.<ref>{{cite web |title=Board Operating Policies and Procedures |url=http://reportcenter.thecb.state.tx.us/reports/data/board-operating-policies-and-procedures-april-2019/.pdf |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=27 April 2020 |pages=4-5}}</ref> The board appoints the Commissioner of Higher Education who serves as the Chief Executive Officer of the Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board.<ref name=\"BC\">{{cite web |title=Board/Commissioner |url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/about-us/board-commissioner/ |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=27 April 2020}}</ref> The current commissioner is Harrison Keller, who assumed the post on October 1, 2019.<ref name=\"BC\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Harrison Keller will be Texas' next higher education commissioner |url=https://www.texastribune.org/2019/09/11/harrison-keller-higher-education-texas/ |accessdate=27 April 2020 |publisher=The Texas Tribune |date=September 11, 2019}}</ref> He succeeded Raymund Paredes, who had been the commissioner since 2004.<ref>{{cite news |title=Raymund Paredes, Texas Higher Education Commissioner, resigns |url=https://www.chron.com/news/houston-texas/houston/article/Raymund-Paredes-Texas-Higher-Education-13559489.php |accessdate=27 April 2020 |publisher=Houston Chronicle |date=January 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Raymund Paredes, Texas' higher education commissioner, will step down Aug. 31 |url=https://www.texastribune.org/2019/01/24/raymund-paredes-states-higher-education-commissioner-will-step-down-au/ |accessdate=27 April 2020 |publisher=The Texas Tribune |date=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Board chairs ==\n* [[Pamela Willeford]], 1998\u20132003\n* [[Robert Shepard]], 2003\u20132009\n* [[A. W. \"Whit\" Riter]], 2009\u20132011\n* [[Fred W. Heldenfels IV]], 2011\u20132013\n* [[Harold W. Hahn]], 2013\u2013\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Texas|Education}}\n* [[Massachusetts Department of Higher Education]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n* [http://www.thecb.state.tx.us Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board] website\n{{State agencies of Texas}}\n{{Public universities in Texas}}\n{{Community colleges in Texas}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:State agencies of Texas|Higher Education Coordinating Board, Texas]]\n[[Category:Education in Texas]]\n\n\n{{Texas-stub}}\n{{Texas-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2009}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox government agency\n|name            = Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board\n|logo            = \n|logo_width      = \n|logo_caption    = \n|motto           = \n|seal            = \n|seal_width      =\n|seal_caption    = \n|formed          = {{start date|1965}}\n|preceding1      =\n|jurisdiction    =\n|headquarters    = [[Austin, Texas]], [[U.S.]]\n|employees       = 233\n|budget          = \n|chief1_name     = Harrison Keller\n|chief1_position = Commissioner\n|chief2_name     =\n|chief2_position =\n|date1           =\n|date1_name      =\n|department      =\n|child1_agency   =\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.thecb.state.tx.us|www.thecb.state.tx.us}}\n}}\n\n[[File:THECBAustinTX.JPG|thumb|Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board headquarters]]\n\n{{Education in the U.S.}}\nThe '''Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board''' ('''THECB''') is an agency of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Texas]]'s government that oversees all public post-secondary education in the state. It is headquartered at 1200 East Anderson Lane in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Welcome to the Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/ |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\nTHECB determines which Texas public four-year universities are permitted to start or continue degree programs. THECB also evaluates degrees from other states and other nations for use in Texas. However, operations of the various universities or systems are the responsibility of each university or system [[board of regents]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Agency Mission, Vision, Philosophy, Core Values, & Key Functions |url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/about-us/board-commissioner/agency-mission-vision-philosophy-core-values-key-functions/ |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 1998 to 2003, it developed a new higher-education plan for the state, called \"Closing the Gaps by 2015\". The plan's stated goal is closing education gaps within Texas, as well as between Texas and other U.S. states. The four main goals of closing the gap is to close the gaps in student participation, student success, excellence and research. Approximately 47,500 additional students will need to enroll at public, independent, and career institutions in fall 2015 to reach the final goal of adding about 630,000 students since fall 2000.\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Closing the Gaps 2015 Progress Report|url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/index.cfm?objectid=858D2E7C-F5C8-97E9-0CDEB3037C1C2CA3|website=The Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe board consists of nine members and one non\u2013voting student representative, all of whom are appointed by the [[Governor of Texas]] on a staggered basis. The terms for the voting members are for six years, ending on August 31 of odd-numbered years while the student representative serves a one year term.<ref>{{cite web |title=Board Operating Policies and Procedures |url=http://reportcenter.thecb.state.tx.us/reports/data/board-operating-policies-and-procedures-april-2019/.pdf |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=27 April 2020 |pages=4-5}}</ref> The board appoints the Commissioner of Higher Education who serves as the Chief Executive Officer of the Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board.<ref name=\"BC\">{{cite web |title=Board/Commissioner |url=http://www.thecb.state.tx.us/about-us/board-commissioner/ |website=Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board |accessdate=27 April 2020}}</ref> The current commissioner is Harrison Keller, who assumed the post on October 1, 2019.<ref name=\"BC\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Harrison Keller will be Texas' next higher education commissioner |url=https://www.texastribune.org/2019/09/11/harrison-keller-higher-education-texas/ |accessdate=27 April 2020 |publisher=The Texas Tribune |date=September 11, 2019}}</ref> He succeeded Raymund Paredes, who had been the commissioner since 2004.<ref>{{cite news |title=Raymund Paredes, Texas Higher Education Commissioner, resigns |url=https://www.chron.com/news/houston-texas/houston/article/Raymund-Paredes-Texas-Higher-Education-13559489.php |accessdate=27 April 2020 |publisher=Houston Chronicle |date=January 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Raymund Paredes, Texas' higher education commissioner, will step down Aug. 31 |url=https://www.texastribune.org/2019/01/24/raymund-paredes-states-higher-education-commissioner-will-step-down-au/ |accessdate=27 April 2020 |publisher=The Texas Tribune |date=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Board chairs ==\n* [[Pamela Willeford]], 1998\u20132003\n* [[Robert Shepard]], 2003\u20132009\n* [[A. W. \"Whit\" Riter]], 2009\u20132011\n* [[Fred W. Heldenfels IV]], 2011\u20132013\n* [[Harold W. Hahn]], 2013\u2013\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Texas|Education}}\n* [[Massachusetts Department of Higher Education]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n* [http://www.thecb.state.tx.us Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board] website\n{{State agencies of Texas}}\n{{Public universities in Texas}}\n{{Community colleges in Texas}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:State agencies of Texas|Higher Education Coordinating Board, Texas]]\n[[Category:Education in Texas]]\n\n\n{{Texas-stub}}\n{{Texas-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lamanomia", "label": "safe", "comment": "cr verb tense \"is\" to \"was\" to reflect completed plan", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas_Higher_Education_Coordinating_Board"}
